ons of madness in transatlantic perspectives. This book will be highly relevant to scholars interested in law, medicine, psychiatry and madness studies, as well as contemporary issues in mental capacity and guardianship.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aInsanity (Law). 0aMental health lawszEngland. 0aMental health lawszGreat BritainxHistory. 0aMental health lawszNew JerseyxHistory. 0aMental health laws. 0aMental illnessxHistory. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aEngland.  aNew Jersey.  aasylum.  acivil law.  acolonies.  acourt.  aguardianship.  amadness.  amental capacity.  atrials.1 aMoran, James E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2019 eBook-Packagez978311128249740uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152613304540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526133045423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526133045/original  a978-3-11-128249-7  Manchester University Press 2019 eBook-Packageb2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles